{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1722,"text":"So I want to talk today\nabout money and happiness,"},{"time":4159,"text":"which are two things a lot of us\nspend a lot of our time thinking about,"},{"time":7741,"text":"either trying to earn them\nor trying to increase them."},{"time":10595,"text":"And a lot of us resonate with this phrase,"},{"time":12898,"text":"we see it in religions\nand self-help books:"},{"time":15731,"text":"money can't buy happiness."},{"time":17050,"text":"And I want to suggest today\nthat, in fact, that's wrong."}]},{"cues":[{"time":19849,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":21924,"text":"I'm at a business school,\nso that's what we do."},{"time":24165,"text":"So that's wrong,"},{"time":25342,"text":"and in fact, if you think that,\nyou're just not spending it right."},{"time":28589,"text":"So instead of spending it\nthe way you usually spend it,"},{"time":31261,"text":"maybe if you spent it differently,\nthat might work a little bit better."},{"time":34772,"text":"Before I tell you the ways you can spend\nit that will make you happier,"},{"time":38241,"text":"let's think about the ways\nwe usually spend it"},{"time":40448,"text":"that don't, in fact, make us happier."},{"time":42284,"text":"We had a little natural experiment."},{"time":44044,"text":"So CNN, a little while ago,\nwrote this interesting article"},{"time":46851,"text":"on what happens to people\nwhen they win the lottery."},{"time":49367,"text":"It turns out people think\nwhen they win the lottery"},{"time":51829,"text":"their lives will be amazing."},{"time":53210,"text":"This article's about\nhow their lives get ruined."},{"time":55544,"text":"What happens when people win the lottery"},{"time":57489,"text":"is, one, they spend\nall the money and go into debt;"},{"time":59911,"text":"and two, all of their friends\nand everyone they've ever met"},{"time":63003,"text":"find them and bug them for money."},{"time":64772,"text":"It ruins their social\nrelationships, in fact."},{"time":66968,"text":"So they have more debt\nand worse friendships"},{"time":69076,"text":"than they had before they won the lottery."}]},{"cues":[{"time":71127,"text":"What was interesting\nabout the article was,"},{"time":73171,"text":"people started commenting\non the article, readers of the thing."},{"time":76187,"text":"And instead of talking\nabout how it made them realize"},{"time":78723,"text":"that money doesn't lead to happiness,"},{"time":80545,"text":"everyone started saying, \"You know\nwhat I'd do if I won the lottery ...?\""},{"time":84013,"text":"and fantasizing about what they'd do."},{"time":85836,"text":"Here's just two of the ones we saw\nthat are interesting to think about."},{"time":89230,"text":"One person wrote, \"When I win,\nI'm going to buy my own little mountain"},{"time":92590,"text":"and have a little house on top.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":94182,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":95521,"text":"And another person wrote,\n\"I would fill a big bathtub with money"},{"time":98594,"text":"and get in the tub\nwhile smoking a big fat cigar"},{"time":100858,"text":"and sipping a glass of champagne.\""},{"time":102728,"text":"This is even worse:\n\"... then I'd have a picture taken"},{"time":105312,"text":"and dozens of glossies made."},{"time":106680,"text":"Anyone begging for money\nor trying to extort from me"},{"time":109200,"text":"would receive a copy\nof the picture and nothing else.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":111975,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":114444,"text":"And so many of the comments\nwere exactly of this type,"},{"time":117041,"text":"where people got money\nand, in fact, it made them antisocial."},{"time":120333,"text":"So I told you it ruins people's lives\nand their friends bug them."},{"time":123545,"text":"Also, money often makes\nus feel very selfish"},{"time":125761,"text":"and we do things only for ourselves."},{"time":127600,"text":"We thought maybe the reason money\ndoesn't make us happy"},{"time":130240,"text":"is that we're spending it\non the wrong things;"},{"time":132436,"text":"in particular, we're always\nspending it on ourselves."},{"time":134986,"text":"And we wondered what would happen"},{"time":136597,"text":"if we made people spend\nmore of their money on others."},{"time":139161,"text":"So instead of being antisocial\nwith your money,"},{"time":141408,"text":"what if you were more pro-social with it?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":143435,"text":"We thought, let's make people\ndo it and see what happens."},{"time":146303,"text":"Let's have some people\ndo what they usually do,"},{"time":148529,"text":"spend money on themselves,"},{"time":149831,"text":"and let's make some people\ngive money away,"},{"time":151886,"text":"and measure their happiness\nand see if, in fact, they get happier."},{"time":155024,"text":"The first way we did this was,\none Vancouver morning,"},{"time":157601,"text":"we went out on the campus\nat University of British Columbia,"},{"time":160600,"text":"approached people and said,\n\"Do you want to be in an experiment?\""},{"time":163688,"text":"They said, \"Yes.\""},{"time":164880,"text":"We asked them how happy they were,\nand then gave them an envelope."},{"time":168005,"text":"One of the envelopes\nhad things in it that said,"},{"time":170343,"text":"\"By 5pm today,\nspend this money on yourself.\""},{"time":173362,"text":"We gave some examples\nof what you could spend it on."},{"time":175959,"text":"Other people got\na slip of paper that said,"},{"time":178048,"text":"\"By 5pm today, spend this money\non somebody else.\""},{"time":181187,"text":"Also inside the envelope was money."}]},{"cues":[{"time":183401,"text":"And we manipulated\nhow much money we gave them;"},{"time":185636,"text":"some people got this slip\nof paper and five dollars,"},{"time":188287,"text":"some got this slip\nof paper and 20 dollars."},{"time":190923,"text":"We let them go about their day\nand do whatever they wanted."},{"time":193954,"text":"We found out they did spend it\nin the way we asked them to."},{"time":196955,"text":"We called them up and asked them,\n\"What did you spend it on?"},{"time":199896,"text":"How happy do you feel now?\""},{"time":201236,"text":"What did they spend it on?"},{"time":202511,"text":"These are college undergrads;"},{"time":203932,"text":"a lot of what they spent it on\nfor themselves"},{"time":206071,"text":"were things like earrings and makeup."},{"time":207891,"text":"One woman said she bought\na stuffed animal for her niece."},{"time":210594,"text":"People gave money to homeless people."},{"time":212397,"text":"Huge effect here of Starbucks."}]},{"cues":[{"time":214464,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":216212,"text":"So if you give\nundergraduates five dollars,"},{"time":218252,"text":"it looks like coffee to them,"},{"time":219674,"text":"and they run over to Starbucks\nand spend it as fast as they can."},{"time":222746,"text":"Some people bought coffee for themselves,\nthe way they usually would,"},{"time":226080,"text":"but others bought coffee\nfor somebody else."},{"time":228223,"text":"So the very same purchase,"},{"time":229923,"text":"just targeted toward yourself\nor targeted toward somebody else."},{"time":233261,"text":"What did we find when we called\nat the end of the day?"},{"time":235848,"text":"People who spent money\non others got happier;"},{"time":238007,"text":"people who spent it on themselves,\nnothing happened."},{"time":240521,"text":"It didn't make them less happy,\nit just didn't do much for them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":243573,"text":"The other thing we saw is the amount\nof money doesn't matter much."},{"time":246700,"text":"People thought 20 dollars\nwould be way better than five."},{"time":249369,"text":"In fact, it doesn't matter\nhow much money you spent."},{"time":251850,"text":"What really matters\nis that you spent it on somebody else"},{"time":254570,"text":"rather than on yourself."},{"time":255765,"text":"We see this again and again"},{"time":257095,"text":"when we give people money to spend\non others instead of on themselves."},{"time":260477,"text":"Of course, these are\nundergraduates in Canada --"},{"time":262767,"text":"not the world's most\nrepresentative population."},{"time":265006,"text":"They're also fairly wealthy and affluent\nand other sorts of things."}]},{"cues":[{"time":268184,"text":"We wanted to see if this holds true\neverywhere in the world"},{"time":270974,"text":"or just among wealthy countries."},{"time":272543,"text":"So we went to Uganda\nand ran a very similar experiment."},{"time":275373,"text":"Imagine, instead of just people\nin Canada, we say,"},{"time":277750,"text":"\"Name the last time you spent\nmoney on yourself or others."},{"time":280532,"text":"Describe it. How happy did it make you?\""},{"time":282473,"text":"Or in Uganda, \"Name the last time\nyou spent money on yourself or others"},{"time":285915,"text":"and describe that.\""},{"time":287096,"text":"Then we asked them\nhow happy they are, again."},{"time":289281,"text":"And what we see is sort of amazing,"},{"time":290985,"text":"because there's human universals\non what you do with your money,"},{"time":294054,"text":"and real cultural differences\non what you do as well."},{"time":296565,"text":"So for example, one guy\nfrom Uganda says this:"},{"time":299893,"text":"\"I called a girl I wished to love.\""},{"time":301793,"text":"They basically went out on a date,"},{"time":303600,"text":"and he says at the end\nthat he didn't \"achieve\" her up till now."}]},{"cues":[{"time":306876,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":308064,"text":"Here's a guy from Canada."},{"time":310059,"text":"Very similar thing."},{"time":311790,"text":"\"I took my girlfriend out for dinner."},{"time":313805,"text":"We went to a movie, we left early,"},{"time":315670,"text":"and then went back to her room\nfor ... cake,\" just cake."}]},{"cues":[{"time":319493,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":320871,"text":"Human universal:"},{"time":322048,"text":"you spend money on others,\nyou're being nice."},{"time":324308,"text":"Maybe you have something\nin mind, maybe not."},{"time":326397,"text":"But then we see extraordinary differences."},{"time":328473,"text":"So look at these two."},{"time":329650,"text":"This is a woman from Canada."},{"time":331028,"text":"We say, \"Name a time you spent\nmoney on somebody else.\""},{"time":333628,"text":"She says, \"I bought a present for my mom."},{"time":335629,"text":"I drove to the mall, bought\na present, gave it to my mom.\""},{"time":338379,"text":"Perfectly nice thing to do."},{"time":339706,"text":"It's good to get gifts\nfor people you know."},{"time":341785,"text":"Compare that to this woman from Uganda:"},{"time":344141,"text":"\"I was walking and met a longtime friend\nwhose son was sick with malaria."},{"time":347859,"text":"They had no money, they went to a clinic\nand I gave her this money.\""},{"time":351257,"text":"This isn't $10,000,\nit's the local currency."},{"time":353490,"text":"So it's a very small\namount of money, in fact."},{"time":355706,"text":"But enormously different motivations here."},{"time":357839,"text":"This is a real medical need,\nliterally a lifesaving donation."},{"time":361391,"text":"Above, it's just kind of,\nI bought a gift for my mother."}]},{"cues":[{"time":364163,"text":"What we see again, though,"},{"time":365798,"text":"is that the specific way you spend\non other people isn't nearly as important"},{"time":369472,"text":"as the fact that you spend on other people\nin order to make yourself happy,"},{"time":373446,"text":"which is really quite important."},{"time":375029,"text":"So you don't have to do\namazing things with your money"},{"time":377594,"text":"to make yourself happy."},{"time":378769,"text":"You can do small, trivial things and still\nget the benefits from doing this."},{"time":382396,"text":"These are only two countries."},{"time":383829,"text":"We wanted to look at every country\nin the world if we could,"},{"time":386802,"text":"to see what the relationship is\nbetween money and happiness."}]},{"cues":[{"time":389725,"text":"We got data from the Gallup Organization,"},{"time":391733,"text":"which you know from\nall the political polls happening lately."},{"time":394632,"text":"They asked people, \"Did you donate\nmoney to charity recently?\""},{"time":397589,"text":"and, \"How happy are you\nwith life in general?\""},{"time":399786,"text":"We can see what the relationship is\nbetween those two things."},{"time":402687,"text":"Are they positively correlated,\ngiving money makes you happy?"},{"time":405623,"text":"Or are they negatively correlated?"},{"time":407287,"text":"On this map, green will mean\nthey're positively correlated,"},{"time":410106,"text":"red means they're negatively correlated."},{"time":412050,"text":"And you can see,\nthe world is crazily green."},{"time":414171,"text":"So in almost every country in the world\nwhere we have this data,"},{"time":417458,"text":"people who give money\nto charity are happier people"},{"time":419939,"text":"than people who don't give\nmoney to charity."},{"time":422093,"text":"I know you're looking\nat the red country in the middle."},{"time":424731,"text":"I would be a jerk and not\ntell you what it is,"},{"time":426909,"text":"but it's Central African Republic."},{"time":428568,"text":"You can make up stories."},{"time":429744,"text":"Maybe it's different there\nfor some reason."},{"time":431780,"text":"Just below that to the right\nis Rwanda, though,"},{"time":434018,"text":"which is amazingly green."}]},{"cues":[{"time":435256,"text":"So almost everywhere we look,"},{"time":436666,"text":"we see that giving money away\nmakes you happier"},{"time":439123,"text":"than keeping it for yourself."},{"time":440693,"text":"What about work, which is where\nwe spend the rest of our time,"},{"time":443682,"text":"when we're not with the people we know."},{"time":445568,"text":"We decided to infiltrate some companies\nand do a very similar thing."},{"time":448815,"text":"These are sales teams in Belgium."},{"time":450644,"text":"They work in teams,\ngo out and sell to doctors"},{"time":453717,"text":"and try to get them to buy drugs."},{"time":455317,"text":"We can look and see\nhow well they sell things"},{"time":457487,"text":"as a function of being a member of a team."},{"time":459754,"text":"We give people on some teams some money"},{"time":462384,"text":"\"Spend it however you want on yourself,\""},{"time":464372,"text":"just like we did\nwith the undergrads in Canada."},{"time":466646,"text":"To other teams we say, \"Here's 15 euro.\nSpend it on one of your teammates."},{"time":470340,"text":"Buy them something as a gift\nand give it to them."},{"time":473028,"text":"Then we can see, we've got teams\nthat spend on themselves"},{"time":475752,"text":"and these pro-social teams\nwho we give money to make the team better."},{"time":479547,"text":"The reason I have\na ridiculous pinata there"},{"time":481600,"text":"is one team pooled their money\nand bought a pinata,"},{"time":484039,"text":"they smashed the pinata,\nthe candy fell out and things like that."},{"time":487144,"text":"A silly, trivial thing to do,"},{"time":488608,"text":"but think of the difference on a team\nthat didn't do that at all,"},{"time":491937,"text":"that got 15 euro, put it in their pocket,\nmaybe bought themselves a coffee,"},{"time":495535,"text":"or teams that had\nthis pro-social experience"},{"time":497619,"text":"where they bonded together\nto buy something and do a group activity."},{"time":500934,"text":"What we see is that the teams\nthat are pro-social sell more stuff"},{"time":504027,"text":"than the teams that only got\nmoney for themselves."}]},{"cues":[{"time":506446,"text":"One way to think of it is: for every\n15 euro you give people for themselves,"},{"time":510113,"text":"they put it in their pocket and don't do\nanything different than before."},{"time":513545,"text":"You don't get money from that;"},{"time":515010,"text":"you lose money, since it doesn't\nmotivate them to perform better."},{"time":518113,"text":"But when you give them 15 euro\nto spend on their teammates,"},{"time":520939,"text":"they do so much better on their teams"},{"time":522737,"text":"that you actually get a huge win\non investing this kind of money."}]},{"cues":[{"time":525855,"text":"You're probably thinking\nto yourselves, this is all fine,"},{"time":528561,"text":"but there's a context that's incredibly\nimportant for public policy,"},{"time":531788,"text":"and I can't imagine it would work there."},{"time":533726,"text":"And if he doesn't show me\nthat it works here,"},{"time":535857,"text":"I don't believe anything he said."},{"time":537495,"text":"I know what you're all thinking\nabout are dodgeball teams."}]},{"cues":[{"time":540306,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":541721,"text":"This was a huge criticism that we got,"},{"time":543600,"text":"that if you can't show it\nwith dodgeball teams, this is all stupid."},{"time":546805,"text":"So we went and found these dodgeball\nteams and infiltrated them,"},{"time":551012,"text":"and did the exact same thing as before."},{"time":552914,"text":"So we give people on some teams\nmoney to spend on themselves."},{"time":555858,"text":"Other teams, we give them money\nto spend on their dodgeball teammates."},{"time":559600,"text":"The teams that spend money on themselves"},{"time":561600,"text":"have the same winning\npercentages as before."},{"time":563810,"text":"The teams we give the money\nto spend on each other"},{"time":566253,"text":"become different teams;"},{"time":567432,"text":"they dominate the league\nby the time they're done."}]},{"cues":[{"time":570007,"text":"Across all of these different contexts --"},{"time":572040,"text":"your personal life, you work life,\neven things like intramural sports --"},{"time":575672,"text":"we see spending on other people\nhas a bigger return for you"},{"time":578506,"text":"than spending on yourself."},{"time":580504,"text":"So if you think money can't buy happiness,\nyou're not spending it right."},{"time":584329,"text":"The implication isn't you should buy\nthis product instead of that product,"},{"time":587933,"text":"and that's the way\nto make yourself happier."},{"time":590087,"text":"It's that you should stop thinking\nabout which product to buy for yourself,"},{"time":593746,"text":"and try giving some of it\nto other people instead."}]},{"cues":[{"time":596600,"text":"And we luckily have\nan opportunity for you."},{"time":599128,"text":"DonorsChoose.org is a nonprofit\nfor mainly public school teachers"},{"time":603222,"text":"in low-income schools."},{"time":604679,"text":"They post projects like,"},{"time":605996,"text":"\"I want to teach Huckleberry Finn\nand we don't have the books,\""},{"time":609040,"text":"or, \"I want a microscope\nto teach my students science"},{"time":611550,"text":"and we don't have a microscope.\""},{"time":613103,"text":"You and I can go on and buy it for them."},{"time":615078,"text":"The teacher and the kids\nwrite you thank-you notes,"},{"time":617577,"text":"sometimes they send pictures\nof them using the microscope."},{"time":620414,"text":"It's an extraordinary thing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":621784,"text":"Go to the website and start yourself\non the process of thinking"},{"time":624924,"text":"less about \"How can I spend\nmoney on myself?\""},{"time":627052,"text":"and more about \"If I've got\nfive dollars or 15 dollars,"},{"time":629933,"text":"what can I do to benefit other people?\""},{"time":632102,"text":"Ultimately, when you do that, you'll find\nyou benefit yourself much more."}]},{"cues":[{"time":635612,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":636827,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}